descript.abstract: Spatial representation of the Primary Moose Range in Minnesota, as delineated by MNDNR Section of Wildlife, Field and Research Staff.
descript.purpose: This dataset should be used for regional or landscape scale analysis and mapping. It should not be used for site level work.
descript.supplinf: Northeast Minnesota covering portions of Cook, Lake, and St. Louis Counties.

dataqual.logic: The polygon contains no overlaps or gaps.

horizpa.horizpar: Data were collected using methods that have unknown accuracy.

procstep.procdesc: Wildlife Biologists created a line shapefile representing the boundary of the estimated moose range based on current harvest and survey data.
Wildlife GIS Staff created a polygon representation fromt the line work. The outer boundary was snapped to Moose Zones where appropriate.
